[[Image:Peter Beyer 2013.jpg|thumb|Peter Beyer (2013)]]

'''Peter Beyer LL.M.''' (born 25 Dezember 1970 in [[Ratingen]], [[Germany]]) is a German politician ([[Christian Democratic Union (Germany)|CDU]]).

== Life ==
After finishing his [[Abitur]] in 1991, he completed his [[Bundeswehr|military service]] in [[Wuppertal]]. Beyer then studied law at the Universities of [[University of D<U+00FC>sseldorf|D<U+00FC>sseldorf]] and [[University of Bonn|Bonn]]. Furthermore, he attended lectures in History and Politics in Bonn. In 1999 he finished his studies and was [[Bar examination|admitted to the bar]]. In 2000 he enrolled in a post-graduate legal studies program at the [[University of Virginia]] [[University of Virginia School of Law|School of Law]] in [[Charlottesville]] where he completed a [[Master of Laws]] in 2001. Returning to Germany, Beyer practiced law at the BEYER Intellectual Poperty firm in [[Ratingen]]. There, he became on of the country's first officially-certified intellectual property specialists.<ref>[http://peter-beyer.info/image/inhalte/file/Bio%20Peter%20Beyer%20engl%20(Aug%202014).pdf English Resum<U+00E9>] on Beyer's official website</ref>

Beyer lives in the German town of Ratingen and has two school-aged children.

== Political career ==
In the [[German federal election, 2009|federal election]] on September 27, 2009, Beyer was elected as a Member of the [[Bundestag]]. He won his in district "Mettmann II" (consisting of the cities of [[Heiligenhaus]], [[Ratingen]], [[Velbert]] und [[W<U+00FC>lfrath]]) with a relative majority of 39,8% of the votes.<ref>[http://www.bundeswahlleiter.de/en/bundestagswahlen/BTW_BUND_09/ergebnisse/wahlkreisergebnisse/l05/wk106/index.html Final result for the constituency, 2009 elections], on the official website of the [[Federal Returning Officer]]</ref>

In the [[German federal election, 2013|federal election]] on September 22, 2013, Beyer was re-elected as a Member of the [[Bundestag]], winning his district with a 45,6% relative majority.<ref>[http://www.bundeswahlleiter.de/en/bundestagswahlen/BTW_BUND_13/ergebnisse/wahlkreisergebnisse/l05/wk105/index.html Final result for the constituency, 2013 elections], on the official website of the [[Federal Returning Officer]]</ref> Currently, he is a member of the Bundestag's Comittee on Foreign Affairs where he serves as Parlamentary Special Rapporteur on Transatlantic Relations.

Beyer describes himself as "comitted Atlanticist" and "advocate of a strong transatlantic relationsship". He is a member of the [[Atlantik-Br<U+00FC>cke]] (engl. ''Atlantic Bridge''), and of the [[Deutsche Gesellschaft f<U+00FC>r ausw<U+00E4>rtige Politik]] (engl. ''German Council on Foreign Relations''), both private [[Think Tank]]s.<ref>[http://peter-beyer.info/image/inhalte/file/Bio%20Peter%20Beyer%20engl%20(Aug%202014).pdf English Resum<U+00E9>] on Beyer's official website</ref>

